Chills began and I felt extremely cold, my head felt "foggy" and tight, ringing in ears started and headache moved to migraine level.  Slight fever 99.8. Main dizziness did pass after about 2 hours but other things continue to linger on an off.  I just feel "off".  I have actually heard other seniors mention some of these very symptoms so am not super alarmed, however, I did not have any of these side effects before the vaccine for Covid-19.  I did experience extreme fatigue and bad headaches since I received the first dose on January 27, 2021.    I have not called my doctor regarding these side effects since I have heard many seniors complain of very similar reactions.  I have rested as much as possible, tried to stay hydrated, and taken Tylenol when needed.  For the dizziness I tried to stay as still as possible and put my head between my knees until it finally passed.

My father passed away on February 10th, 2021. On Monday, January 25th 2021, he said he is feeling very uncomfortable in his chest area. He thought it was severe acid reflux. He took Gas X for Acid Reflux and told us that he does not want to go to the hospital. On Tuyesday, January 26th, he felt that his Acid Reflux symptoms got worse, he still did not want to go to the hospital. He took Tums. On that evening, he started having shortness of breath. We took his BP at home and it was very low. We begged him to go to the hospital, he still did not want to go. On Wednesday, January 27th, his shortness of breath got worse and we convinced him that he has to go to the hospital. We took him to ER. Doctor said that he had a heart attack on Monday morning and that is why he was not feeling well since Monday morning. While at the hospital, while the cardiologists were monitoring him, his heart condition got worse.  By Friday, February 5th, cardiologists said that he is very fragile, his heart condition is very fragile and he won't survive any procedure. They said that something triggered the heart attack. We told them about the vaccination on 1/13/2021. They sent him home on hospice on Friday, Feburary 5th, 2021. He was on supplemental oxygen when he came home. He passed away due to a heart attack on February 10th, 2021 around 9pm.
CUR_ILL: Heart Problem, High Blood Pressure, Arthritis

SYMPTOM_TEXT: When driving home following 15 minute wait period I felt my throat tighten, ears flush and heart rate increasing.  I immediately began to monitor my heart rate with my Watch.  My resting heart rate is in the 60?s.  At the time I looked at the watch my heart rate was already in the low 100?s but was rapidly escalating until in a matter of a few minutes had reached 140 bpm and my head began to have a full sensation and I was  becoming very shaky.  I pulled over into the parking lot of a restaurant and asked them to call 911.  As they were talking with the dispatch my pulse started to decline so I cancelled the request.  I stayed at the restaurant until friends to could come pick me up.  By the time they arrived my pulse was in the low 100?s.  I took 2 Benadryl.  I monitored my BP through the night and it did not return to the 60?s until 1:00 am.   I took (2) 25 mg Benadryl at approximately 4:00 pm,  took another 2 at around 9:00 pm when my heart rate started to escalate and then a final 2 before going to bed at 1:00 am.  My pulse dropped back into the 60?s while I was sleeping and stayed that way through the night.  I woke up with no further symptoms nor side effects from the shot.  The throat tightness and flushing of the ears resolved after the first dose of Benadryl.  I had no adverse reactions or significant side effects from he first dose of Pfizer.
LAB_DATA: Did not see a doctor however I have reported the situation to my primary care doctor.

Headache, aches within 8 hours. Within 20 hours developed severe vertigo and nausea. Movement caused room spinning and broke out in cold sweat. Severe vertigo continued through second day (Feb 22), but seemed to diminish somewhat toward evening. Day 3 still had moderate vertigo/nausea but better than previous day. Went on a long walk. Day 4 moderate vertigo/nausea continued. Tried doing Epley exercises for vertigo. Vertigo/nausea became severe again, so severe I vomited several times. After vomiting got the shakes and felt very cold. Checked blood pressure and it was very high (170/98), but pulse rate was in low 30s. After a few hours blood pressure and pulse rate became closer to normal. Almost decided to go to ER clinic, but decided to wait until my daughter came home from work because I was way too dizzy to drive. After I calmed down I decided it wasn't an emergency. Severe vertigo continued through evening of day 4. On day 4 I called primary care doctor to see if there was anything I could do for the vertigo. She prescribed meclizine, but hearing that it is an antihistamine, I declined it (antihistamines make my heart race and make me very anxious). Severe vertigo/nausea continued through day 5 and day 6. (Severe vertigo/nausea being that I could not move around at all other than to sit still staring forward without the room spinning.) All this period I also had a headache, a feeling of pressure through my whole head/sinus area, and my vision was blurred. I also felt as though I could not focus my eyes or concentration. I tried using some over-the-counter nasal decongestant spray for 2 days to relieve congestion in head, but they made me feel very anxious, so I stopped. I also tried taking some Aleve a couple of times. It helped a little, but made me feel woozy, so stopped. Day 6 the vertigo/nausea improved to moderate, but I could still not walk straight. I felt unsafe to drive. Day 7 continued to improve, but still moderate vertigo/nausea. Day 8 I noticed a lot of improvement in vertigo/nausea. Kept improving day 9. By evening on day 10 I was noticing a rawness and lump in the back of my throat. Called primary care office day 11 to see someone. Drove car, but felt marginally safe driving. Was diagnosed with a sinus infection and prescribed a 10 day course of Amoxicillin/Clavulanic Acid (875-125 mg for 2 pills a day for 10 days). Felt improvement in throat and sinus over next few days. Day 15 I felt greatly improved with head ?fog? and vertigo. Had an appointment with an ENT clinic on day 15 to see what was causing vertigo. All tests were good for hearing, and visual examination of ears. Was checked for BPV but that was ruled out. Said vertigo was probably caused by viral infection or inflammation of vestibular nerve or canals. Recommended waiting for improvement and coming back if it persisted. Began doing more normal activities even though I still had mild vertigo. Day 16 felt still better in morning, then in afternoon bent over quickly to catch something and got a terrible wave of spinning again. Moderate/severe vertigo continued that evening. Improved to moderate on day 17 and 18. All along, when vertigo was worse, so was the ?fog? (blurry vision, inability to focus mentally). At day 19 I feel like I did on day 15, but I have noticed the pressure/lump around my ear and on left side of head is improved. Brain ?fog? is improved too, very mild and the vertigo is mild. I finish my antibiotic tomorrow.At present vertigo is not gone. Its mild today, but this is only one of maybe 2 1/2 days in which its been this mild (out of almost three weeks since I was vaccinated). I have been drinking a lot of water every day, and ginger tea when I get nauseous. I had my 2nd dose of the COVID Pfizer vaccine scheduled for Mar 15. I?ve cancelled it and intend to wait to see how long it takes for vertigo to finally resolve before considering a 2nd dose.
LAB_DATA: ENT exam of ears and hearing March 15, 2021 No evident issues.

HISTORY: Arthritis, low thyroid (without meds), hypertension (without meds), prediabetic
ALLERGIES: Tetracycline and Demerol make me nauseous

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient had dark circles under their eyes and did discuss at the drop off window they had a needle phobia. Immediately after the immunization, he said he felt lightheaded. I, pharmacist, sat in the booth and talked to him for a couple minutes then asked if he felt he could finish his observation outside the booth.  I notified technician to hand him off to her for observation , sharing by observation that the patient did not look well but he said he was doing a little better. He said he felt better and he did wait in the chairs outside the immunization booth. While I was in the pharmacy discussing this information with my pharmacy technician when I heard yelling and I stepped back out of the pharmacy to observe the patient was sliding out of his chair, stiff straight. My other technician came to my assistance and we both tried to get him to the floor and he was making incoherent noises and his arm was bent behind him and not relaxing to where we could get him to the floor. He then came to and startled a bit, with a bewildered look on his face. He asked what happened and said he felt he was dreaming.  A witness waiting on her prescriptions for pickup said that it originally appeared he was having a seizure which was my concern as well. We called code white and 911 and store manager assisted us at the scene. Patient denied the ambulance.
PRIOR_VAX: tetanus and blood draw

About 2 hours after receiving the vaccine, I became very nauseated.  I than begin vomiting.  I vomited probably around 7-8 times (maybe more), and the last 2 times there was nothing left in my stomach to come up and I was just heaving.  I also had moderately severe lower abdomen cramps (just above my pelvic bone).  It felt like my insides were twisting at times, and the pain was constant cramping with moments of pretty severe twisting doubling over pain. I had chills just before the vomiting started, and felt like I had a slight fever, but because of the constant nausea/vomiting I did not take my temperature (all I have is an oral thermometer). To get the pain to stop, I had to lay down on a bed and put pressure on my stomach sides to ease the cramping. I tried taking Pepto-bismol to stop the nausea and vomiting, but immediately vomited that up too. The vomiting finally stopped after 2 times of dry heaving and nothing left to come up.  The severe lower abdomen stomach cramping calmed down around 1 or 2 am. Today I feel weak, my right arm is very sore and slightly swollen, and as of the time of this report at 2:30pm I have only eaten some saltine crackers today. My stomach still feels weak, even though the nausea, cramping, and vomiting have gone away now.
LAB_DATA: None. But I am quite worried about whether I should take the 2nd dose of the vaccine or not after what happened.  I don't know if this was normal for a 1st dose or not. My husband called the on-call physician for our doctors practice to see if I should be worried or go to the ER.
HISTORY: Restrictive Lung Disease, spinal stenosis, muscle weakness and fatigue, chronic muscle pain, walking difficulties and walk with a cane. The restrictive lung disease is bad enough that I have to sleep in a recliner sitting up every night in order to breathe.
ALLERGIES: Have had prior allergic reactions to Penicillin and Tomatoes. Both resolved a few years later, and I have been prescribed Penicillin without any problems. I also regularly eat tomatoes now too with no problems.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt is a 59 year old male who presented to the community center for Moderna vaccination. After receiving an intramuscular shot at his left arm he began to feel numbness and heaviness in his left arm, 3-4 minutes post injection. Pt stated he had associated light headedness and fatigue. Pts vitals were taken with 140/90 BP, HR 84, SPo2 97-98 %. Pts vitals were retaken and he became tachycardia with HR ranging from 130-125. PT stated his symptoms worsened and the paramedics were called at that time. PT received 125mg solumedrol to upper outer quadrant of left gluteal area. Paramedics arrived on scene within 10 minutes of onset of symptoms. Physical - General - Anxious , sweating   Cardiac - Tachycardia, no murmurs, rubs, or gallops. Resp - clear to auscultation B/L ABD - soft non-tender, non distended, bs + in all 4 quadrants. Presyncope rule out cardiogenic vs. neurogenic causes, pt was taken to the emergency room via paramedics secondary to what was described in the HPI. Pt was taken to hospital.
ALLERGIES: Not severe allergic reaction or Hx of vaccination reactions.

On Friday morning I started having chest pains. The pains were sharp and would go away quickly. (Almost immediately) They were from the center of my chest to the right of my chest at about the same level as my heart, I could tell that the pains were NOT coming from my heart, or at least, that is how it seemed. I also felt some pains to the left of the center of my chest, but the pains from the left were fewer and not as pronounced. These pains resulted in my leaving work early (I was on the way to work when they started) and I stayed home from work today. The pains did not continue for more than 4  hours or so, and seemed to dissipate later that day. I did feel some discomfort in my chest this morning. This discomfort was extremely mild and did not last much more than an hour and a half. I feel fine this afternoon, as I am writing this note. I have been eating, urinating and have had normal bowl movements today, so I think I am okay. You might be mindful of these chest pains the Moderna vaccine is causing. The pains were sharp and noticeable. I did not call my Doctor because it did not seem necessary. Thank you.

Patient received his first dose of Johnson & Johnson today, 03/21/2021 at 1100am, at COVID vaccination clinic.  Patient had received his vaccine and was walking back to his vehicle when he told his mother that he "wasn't feeling well."  Soon thereafter, patient stated that he was experiencing "tunnel vision" and light-headedness and proceeded to have a syncopal episode.  He fell onto his mother who braced his fall.  There was no head trauma.  Patient was then seated in a chair.  Patient stated that he had not eaten or drank anything that day.  Patient states loss of consciousness. Patient states he has never had a similar experience in the past.  He denied a presence of past medical history and denies allergies to medications, foods, and other vaccines.  Upon exam, patient appeared pale and diaphoretic.  Skin color improved to pink following patient sitting and consuming water/food.  Radial pulse was strong, HR 62bpm.  Bilateral lungs clear to ausculation.  No audible wheezing or stridor.  Respirations at 12 per minute.  Initial sitting BP was 108/60.  After 15 minutes, BP improved to 120/80.  EMS was called to provide further resources that were not available onsite, to include a blood glucose level.  Patient denied transport to the local hospital for further evaluation and treatment.
LAB_DATA: HR: 60 Initial BP: 108/60  BP at 10 minutes following interventions: 120/80 RR: 12 per minute HR: 62bpm, strong bounding pulse

Bell's palsy symptoms within an hour after receiving vaccine injection:  consisted of right-sided facial numbness, right-sided eyelid droop, right-sided mouth turn, right-sided tightness in neck muscle, pressure behind right eye, headache, loss of balance, difficulty speaking.  The injection was at 3:15 pm and started with arm soreness and stinging, a slight headache, and some tingling in my right hand while waiting 15 minutes after the shot, I had also felt a sensation going up the right side of the back of my neck almost immediately after the injection.  The Bell's palsy symptoms started by 4:00 pm.  I had a low-grade temp that evening of 99.9.  I emailed my neurologist who I see for migraines, of my symptoms.  The following morning on 03-10-2021 I woke with a severe migraine, fullness in my right ear, more pressure behind my right eye and it is watery, with new ringing in both ears, louder in the right ear.   Still residual numbness and drooping of right side of face and eye, tightness in right side neck muscle in front, and speaking better.   Woke up on Thursday morning 03-11-2021 with flu symptoms and migraine gone.  Eye pressure still there and now having significant pain moving my eye and now more feeling of fullness in my right ear.  Eye pain was concerning.  Dr advised me at this time if symptoms have continued or gotten worse to go to the emergency room.   Today, Saturday 03-13-2021, I am still experiencing moderate eye pain behind/above my right eye with pressure.  I am continuing to treat the pain with oxycodone prescribed by ER Physician.
LAB_DATA: Advised by Neurologist to go to the ER on 03-11-2021 as symptoms had not resolved and gotten worse.  Seen at Emergency Department, treated by Dr who performed a neurological exam, consulted with neurologist Dr, and orded an MRI of Brain/Head with and without contrast.  MRI was clear of stroke or mass.   ER Diagnosis: Right facial pain / Trigeminal neuralgia of right side of face / Migraine without status migrainosus, not intractable, unspecified migraine type / side effects of vaccination, initial encounter.  Treated with oxycodone for eye pain, zofran for nausea,  gadobenate dimeglumine steroids for inflammation.  Followed up with my neurologist Dr.
OTHER_MEDS: Clonidine 0.1mg for high BP Extra Strength Tylenol, Ibuprofen, and Phenergan for migraines

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I was fine when getting the injection and my � hour wait. I was fine during dinner and after dinner and until about 9 hours after the injection when my arm felt exceedingly sore. I had been watching a free Amazon Prime cute movie while knitting a blanket for my grandson. When the movie was over and I was clearing my knitting, I noticed my super sore arm. I got up to check my face in the mirror to be sure that I was not having a reaction. But I did have a reaction with a rash on my chest and face 9 hours after the injection. My arm really hurt for three days but is fine now.  When I saw my red face and chest, I took a Zyrtex D and a Benadryl.  It did not seem to help the redness to go away. When I felt some tightening of my throat and started to feel that I might be starting to lose some clarity of thought, I quickly watched a minute video on how to use my new kind of generic epipen and jabbed myself in the leg and called 911.    I felt much better after the epipen in terms of my thinking and throat.  Basically, the medics that came to the house and said that I had taken what they would give me at the hospital and it was up to me if I wanted to go to the emergency room or not; they would take me but I would need a ride home. With the pandemic and 48 new cases, I decided to stay home and I went to bed; the rash on my face was gone in the morning. The next days I just felt muscle soreness all through my body (day 2) and felt tired (next two days) but had no fever at any time.  I am fine today. I appear to have two very small areas on my chest that probably related to the reaction.
OTHER_MEDS: Zyrtex D, vitamin D3, multiple vitamin for women over 50, vitamin C, fish oil, Bio Complete 3
ALLERGIES: food: severe allergies to turmeric as well as mustard seeds plus severe allergies to hornets (need to use epipen for these items ) allergy shots to reduce year around allergies to all grasses as well as outside mold and dust mites (four times anaphylactic shock for allergy injections over about three years that were stopped by allergist after fourth incidence) rashes to some preservatives and pain medications  never any allergies to flu shots

I experienced fever, chills, tiredness, and headache approximately five hours after administration of the vaccine on 3-10-21. Symptoms became severe within 30 minutes thereafter, at which time I experienced difficulty standing. After five hours with no improvement, I used my home blood pressure monitor to check my BP and HR; BP was high for me, 120/90 sustained, and HR varied between 135 and 150, with 143 being the most consistent value after multiple readings. I seemed to be experiencing a "severe allergic reaction" per the instructions I was given and called 9-1-1. I was transported to Hospital, treated in ER, and then admitted to the intermediate care unit. I was discharged to home on 3-12-21.
LAB_DATA: Multiple labs were drawn. Only the troponin values were critical. Troponin x 4 results were as follows: 3-11-21 4:53 AM - 1.71 ng/mL; 3-11-21 9:31 AM - 1.78 ng/mL; 3-11-21 2:46 PM 1.97 ng/mL, and 3-11-21 7:58 PM - 1.78 ng/mL .  AP Chest x-ray - no acute findings.  12-lead EKG - sinus tachycardia with incomplete right bundle branch block.   Echocardiogram summary: Left ventricular ejection fraction is normal with an estimated ejection fraction of 60-65%; left ventricular segmental wall motion is normal, left ventricular wall thickness is normal; no valvular abnormality.   Per CTA report "The right coronary is dominant with a 20% proximal stenosis. Left main is widely patent. Circumflex is small. The proximal LAD is a good caliber vessel with a large first diagonal. The LAD proper then quickly tapers into a very small caliber vessel and is very difficult to visualize beyond its first 1 cm. Functional analysis demonstrates no wall motion abnormality. Ejection fraction is approximately 68%. Impressions were stated as follows: "The LAD past the first diagonal is diminutive, this may be due to chronic disease, congenital variant or spontaneous coronary artery dissection. The favored diagnosis is SCAD due to the fact that the patient has no other significant atherosclerotic disease seen on the study."  Test for SARS CoV 2 was also performed; SARS CoV 2  was not detected.  Follow up is planned to attempt further visualization of the LAD, if possible, and verify the SCAD diagnosis that was indicated. At discharge, low-dose aspirin 81 mg PO qday and metoprolol succinate XL 25 mg PO qday were prescribed.  Attending physician was MD. Another MD provided cardiology consult.
OTHER_MEDS: Levothyroxin 88 mcg PO qday Minoxidil 5% topical qday

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Arrived home after vaccination - felt very tired and fell asleep.  When I woke around 3:30pm  I was experiencing a very rapid heart beat (tachycardia) and my heart was skipping a beat every 10 seconds or so (arrhythmia).  I took my blood pressure several times, while seated and at rest and it fluctuated between  180/87  with a heart rate of 74, to 150/94 with a heart rate of 111, to  143/98 heart rate 107 and then to 118/77 with a heart rate of 105.  To verify the machine was working, both my husband and son used the same device and their readings were steady and did not fluctuate.  I called my GP, who told me to drink lots of water, rest and wait to see with my heart doctor.  She also said if my condition got worse to go to the ER.   I made an appointment with my heart doctor but he cannot see me until April 7.  The adverse event lasted until bedtime.  (about 6-7 hourse).  I haven't had a problem after that.  I since discovered that the CDC changed its recommendation a couple days before I got the vaccine to avoid the shot if I'm allergic to Polysorbate due to PEG being present in the mRNA vaccines.
LAB_DATA: None yet.  I am scheduled to see a cardiologist on April 7 and am in the process of scheduling an appointment with an immunologist.
OTHER_MEDS: Vitamin D2 (drisdol).  Taking no prescription medications.  Stopped supplements a week before vaccination.  Supplements were a multivitamin and B12.
CUR_ILL: none.  did have a week-long episode of acid reflux or GERD, controlled by diet modification.
ALLERGIES: allergic to polysorbate.  (have never had severe anaphylaxis with polysorbate)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Symptoms: Fainting, Unconciouness (repeatedly), Profusive Sweating, Low Blood Pressure (60 over unknown number), Nausea, Dizziness, Unable to stabilize quickly, not able to get an IV, extreme thirst  Signs: Immediately felt unwell within 5 minutes of the vaccine.  Time Course: Injection (1st dose - Pfizer) at 4:00pm. Adverse Reaction at 4:05/4:10 (est.) Released at 5:00pm (est.)  Description of Incident:  On March 8th, at 4:00 pm, I received my first dose of the covid vaccine. Within 5 to 7 minutes, I felt unwell while sitting in the waiting area. I walked towards a worker to inform them that I was feeling unwell and that I was going to pass out. I became unresponsive and laid on the ground. My husband was with me at the time. I was unconscious for a bit and when I regained consciousness, my legs were being raised. I regained consciousness and was able to recall my name, DOB, and address. After I was done recalling my information, I began to lose consciousness again. They brought a wheelchair and took me to the medical room. As I moved from the wheelchair to the bed, I began to lose consciousness again. They told me to lay down. I overheard a woman ask my husband if I had diabetes or heart problems. He answered ?No.?. She explained to him that my body did not know how to accept the vaccine and was trying to regulate back to normal. She explained that my body was going through ?homeostasis? (?). While I laid on the bed, some workers took my blood pressure and tried to start an IV. One of them made a comment and said I was extremely dehydrated. This was odd to hear because I normally drink 3 to 4 liters of water daily. During this entire medical event, I felt the water pushing out through my pores. I was drenched in sweat. He tried to start an IV on my left arm and was unsuccessful. He tried to start an IV on my right hand, which was also unsuccessful. He stated they were unable to start IV liquids because my veins kept popping/collapsing. My blood pressure was reading 60. They checked it again, still at 60. I laid in the bed and basically waited it out. After a few minutes, they checked my blood pressure at it was at 120. They said that was good and I was good to go. No report was given to me nor my husband about the event that occurred. Even after they agreed to let me use a wheelchair (due to feeling weak), one was not provided to me. They basically stated that I was ?good to go?, after doing a series of hand squeezes and walking a few steps upright. I am currently trying to obtain a copy of the report I saw the gentleman fill out at the time. I was given Zofran to help with my nausea, it was placed under my tongue. After going home, I felt weak, tired and somewhat lightheaded. My husband drove me home and I got some rest. I set an appointment with my doctor on Friday March 12th to determine what happened to me during my vaccine and to record the incident. After describing the incident, she determined that it was anaphylaxis. She recommended for me not to get my second dose due to the anaphylactic shock I experienced with the first dose. She was shocked to learn that they did not transport me to the hospital or provided an Epi Pen injection.  When asked why I didn?t drive myself to the hospital, I let her know that they told me I was ?good?. They did not explain what had occurred to me, no mention of anaphylaxis was explained. I was not aware that is what had occurred. The incident occurred from 4:00pm (injection time) to 5:00pm (left location).
LAB_DATA: None. During the adverse event, it was not treated as anaphylaxis. My primary doctor confirmed this after the adverse event, on Friday, March 12th. After describing my symptoms and the event, she determined that it was anaphylaxis.
CUR_ILL: No illnesses at the time, nor one month prior.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Vaccine was received on 9/19/2019. Within 7 days, I began experiencing extreme fatigue along with some other minor symptoms. Initially, I wrote off the symptoms as being not connected to the vaccine. Within the following 2 weeks, I began having muscle tremors throughout my entire body, including facial. The tremors started out mild then progressed to being much worse (e.g. unable to hold a smile or walk up stairs without significant muscle tremors). Fatigue by this time had become debilitating to the point where I was only able to move around for a few hours at a time.   In December 2019, I went to see my primary care doctor. She had multiple labs performed to rule out other items (such as electrolyte imbalance and some additional more severe possibilities such as parkinsons) as an effect of Hep A vaccine in this way is rare. After ruling out multiple possibilities and seeing no connection with the symptoms, she referred me to Dr. with Neurology.   Dr. was able to see me in February 2020. By this time, the fatigue was so crippling, I was only able to get out of bed 2-3 hours a day with the rest being bedridden. Muscle tremors and extreme muscle weakness had also increased along with mental related problems such as memory issues, focus and the like.  Over the following 12 months, Dr. performed numerous in office tests as well as labs ranging from electrical tests to lab draws to MRI's. After ruling out several issues unrelated to a bad vaccine, such as Myastenia Gravis and other possible related diseases, and after performing a battery of tests, he has diagnosed me with the following:  1. Chronic fatigue - R53.82 (Primary) 2. Mild cognitive impairment with memory loss - G31.84 3. Encephalitis - G04.90  I reported the findings to nurse with epidemiology. Her information is below. I asked her about filing a VAERS report. She sent me the details and said that it would be best to do so personally as the health department is so incredibly overloaded and short staffed at the moment.
LAB_DATA: There have been too many lab and medical tests to account for as the doctors were trying to attempting to rule out other factors as the cause. I started to be quite concerned since it seemed to just keep climbing.  I called EMS and they came by to check on me.  As they had me take deep breaths, it began to go down.  But it took several hours to get back to normal values (@ 8:30 PM  it was finally down to 168/79 and 85).  I had the same reaction with the second vaccine on 3/4/21, but it did not last as long.  It again started about 2 1/2 hours after the shot, but was back to normal by 3:30 PM.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 4 hours after receiving the  Moderna COVID-19 vaccine (left-arm), my mother began to have moderate pain in her left arm, particularly in the left shoulder area. The pain continued to increase throughout the afternoon, until it became so severe (10 on a 10-point pain scale) by 8:30 pm on 3/10/21 , that she could no longer lift her arm. She took 500 mg of Tylenol to attempt to relive the pain and went to bed early.   At 2:45 am on 3/11/21, she needed to go to the restroom, and I (daughter) had to assist her to get out of bed, as she had no use of her left arm due to severe pain in that arm. While seated on the toilet, she indicated that her arm was extremely painful and she felt that she was going to pass out and felt nauseated. Within a minute, she lost consciousness and  I called emergency services. EMT arrived within 5 minutes and stated that her blood pressure was extremely low and she needed to be placed on the floor.  They placed her on a gurney and took her to the ambulance, where they started an IV and took her to her local hospital.  I followed shortly thereafter, where she was taken to the ER. She was admitted to the hospital for observation and given Ativan (she refused any opioids) She was ultimately diagnosed with vasovagal syncope due to the pain in her left arm. Two days later, the pain has subsided.
HISTORY: osteoarthritis, pityriasis rubra pilaris (PRP), degenerative disc disease

The itch began on my left wrist and by the end of the day, the itchy spot on my wrist had progressed to itchiness on the majority of my left arm. It's not very visibly red, but it's incredibly itchy and painful, like fiberglass under my skin. The itch is not obviously localized to the injection site but is on the same arm as the injection and nowhere else on my body. It has lasted for 24 hours, and I currently still have it today (3/14/21). I have taken antihistamines and NSAIDs and applied cortisone cream, but it is still very, very uncomfortable. It kept waking me up while I slept during the night. I am wondering if this could be "COVID arm."

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine EUA  Distortion of vision in both eyes but predominantly in the left eye. First noticed the morning after receiving the vaccine, and unchanged at this time (5 days after vaccination).   The left-eye distortion is along vertical lines, such as when viewing an icon or a box on a computer screen. The distortion is very crisp and unwavering (not flashes or floaters) and forms a very clear half-circle that bends toward the left, as if the line is being pushed to the left by a ball. There are no dark spots or "missing" vision, just that what I'm looking at is pushed to the side at the point where I'm focusing. The right-eye distortion is much smaller but definitely present, and distorts to the right instead of the left.
LAB_DATA: I (patient) was seen by an ophthalmologist 3 days after vaccination (on March 12), a computed tomography exam was performed, and no retinal pathology was found. A follow-up exam is scheduled for April 5.  The ophthalmologist's differential diagnoses were 1) ocular migraine, which it definitely is not, and 2) effect of posterior vitreous detachment, which was found in the left eye on exam. However, I experienced that in my right eye two years ago, and this is NOTHING like that. No floaters, no shimmering or flashing lights, and so far not resolving in any way.

He asked if we would page his wife as well. I gave the patient some water while asking how he was breathing. He said it was just difficult to swallow. He said he didn't have any trouble breathing  but was noticeably shaking. Management came to check in and then went to wait for the ambulance to arrive. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Four hours post vaccine I had muscle and joint pain throughout my entire body and I took 600 mg Advil.  Four hours after that I repeated the 600 mg dose of Advil and went to bed.  I felt feverish and my pain did not diminish despite the medication.  At approximately 2 am I got up to try and cool myself off.  I fainted in my bathroom and fell, hitting my head on the tub, although I did not know this at the time.  I thought I just laid down.  I was unable to get up.  For the next 2 hours I slowly inched myself from the bathroom into the hallway and towards my bed.  I was very cold and in severe pain.  When I reached my bed I finally warmed up and fell asleep.  I was unable to get up out of the bed, except to raise myself on my right elbow to drink a mouthful of water, until approximately 4 pm the following day.   This was 28 hours after the vaccine.  No medications helped my pain, it just slowly subsided on it's own.      For the next 24 hours I was able to get up and use the bathroom and drink some water and juice but I could not eat or perform any function. I could not even sit up in bed.  When I was able to start eating again I had diarrhea for 24 hours.  It has been 5 complete days since the vaccine.  I am still winded while performing simple cleaning tasks.  I need about 2 hours of rest in bed (twice yesterday) just to get through a day with nothing in it.   I did not expect the level of immobility/illness, unalleviated pain or the seriousness of my second vaccine reaction.
CUR_ILL: Previous reaction to first COVID vaccine including muscle/joint pain and severe fatigue, followed by a cold (sneezing, congestion) lasting a total of 7 days.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Six days after receiving vaccine, began feeling unwell. Unable to do usual household tasks and requiring bedrest for much of the day.   The symptoms are very similar to the waves of symptoms I experienced early on in Post-Acute Covid-19 syndrome. I got sick in March and was experiencing waves like this through November. Since November, my physical symptoms had abated and I had not suffered a major relapse like this, besides a mild relapse at end of January. The vaccine seems to have triggered a major relapse in my long covid symptoms.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received the vaccination on Friday and on Sunday my bleeding increased. I already had some mild bleeding that had been constant since Feb 23rd or 24th. But I had an appointment on Feb 26th that confirmed I had a baby with a healthy heartbeat. I was also diagnosed with a very small uterine cyst. They told me the cause of the bleeding was pro ant implantation bleeding.  I had light bleeding (bleeding just needing one or two pant liners each day) until Sunday the  7 when I saw an increase in bleeding. I called my doctor on Tuesday (I decided not to call Monday because I felt I would get the same answer I had already gotten, which was that everything was fine) and they had me come in die an urgent same day appointment. At that appointment I learned my baby did not have a heartbeat. The baby was measuring at just over 8 weeks.  The due date given to me based on my last period was October 12th. So I was exactly 9 weeks when I went into the appointment Tuesday to find out the baby didn?t have a heartbeat.  I officially miscarried the embryo and the placenta on Friday March 12th.  This would have been my second baby. My first is a male and he is 18 months old. My first pregnancy didn?t have any complications. I do not have a history of miscarriage in my family, and this was the first one I have had.  I did have to take 150mg of Clomid to get pregnant with this baby.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Swelling, redness, heat at the injection site after 8 days. No swelling before.

On Saturday 03/13/2021 the patient's mother contacted me.  Due to the patient having a mental disability, the mother described the event.  She stated the patient's arm became very red, swollen, hot, and painful the day after vaccination.  I asked if the patient was having any trouble breathing other signs of anaphylaxis to which the mother responded "no."  I instructed the mother to give the patient Benadryl and to use a cold compress to help with the reaction.  I also told the mother if the patient's condition worsened, showed signs of anaphylaxis, or didn't improve within 3 days to go to her doctor.  On Sunday 03/14/2021 the patient and her mother came to the store and the mother asked me to examine the patient's arm.  There was a noticeable rash 6 inches in diameter.  I felt the arm in comparison to the other arm but did not notice any hardening or warmth.  The mother stated the patient's arm seemed to be improving from the previous day, but that the arm was still red and painful.  At this time, I advised the mother to draw a line around the rash; if it got bigger, she needed to go to the hospital, but if it got smaller that was a good sign that the condition was improving.  I instructed the mother to continue giving the patient Benadryl and using a cold compress.  I also advised that the patient should still receive the second dose of the series, because this was not an anaphylactic reaction.  I also advised the patient to pre-medicate with Benadryl before the second dose.  I told the patient I was going to ollow up with them in a few days.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: This is a report after my 2nd vaccine. I received my 1st vaccine on 2/10/21 [Lot # EL9265].  Both vaccines gave me a reaction, and both around the same time the next morning.   My reaction to my 1st vaccine included slight fever, aches, and chills.  Both doses were administered around 3:30pm and reaction was approximately 10:30-11am the next morning.  On this 2nd dose, roughly 40 minutes after waking from sleep, I became mildly nauseas. I sensed I would vomit, so I sat down on the commode with a bucket in front. I started getting the sweats, got very cold, and my arms starting shaking. I started to feel the room spin, saw big black dots, and after banging on the wall to alert my husband something was happening, I fainted and passed out cold.  My husband saw me fall face down, and after waking me, I was in a panic, did not know where I was, or how I was on the floor. I passed out a 2nd time, at which point, my husband was able to get me to the car and he took me to the local hospital. I was incoherent on the car ride, moaning, and not knowing what was happening. My eyes remained closed until I was wheeled into the emergency area and they asked me my name.  I was taken to a private room, where they hooked up a blood pressure cuff, an oxygenator on my finger, and took several viles of blood. I was then taken to the cat scan room for a brain scan, and several hours later, was given a chest xray.  I remained in the room for approx 6 hours, where I was becoming more and more aware of where I was. I had not eaten/drank anything, except a cup of water. I had not used the lavatory.  The PA came to me hours later stating all my tests came back negative, and they could not determine what happened, xrays and blood tests were good, and cat scan was good.  He said that while they couldn't determine what happened, they would recommend a stay, so they can do more extensive testing.  I contacted my husband via cell, told him what they said, and after another 1 1/2 hours, I made the decision to release myself as I was feeling more like myself again, albeit tired.  I went home that evening, ate a small dinner, went to bed, and by 12 Noon the next day, I was fine again.
LAB_DATA: Blood tests Cat scan Chest xray

SYMPTOM_TEXT: While  patient was sitting in chair waiting her 15 minute monitoring period in post- immunization waiting area patient fainted. Patient did not fall down or was she injured by fainting. Patient slowly rolled off chair and patients friend helped lower her to floor where patient regained her awareness . Pharmacist raced quickly to be by patient's side to monitor her vitals and to see if an allergic/ anaphylactic reaction had occured. No symptoms of an allergic reaction or anaphylaxis was observed by pharmacist. Patient quickly regained her awareness and stated that fainting is common to her when routine blood work, injections, giving blood, etc.. Patient stated that fainting is something that has occurred several times in her past. No signs of allergic reaction, redness, hives, facial swelling, cardiovascular collapse were observed by pharmacist while closely monitoring her vitals after 911 was called. EMTs and paramedics arrived quickly and after closely examining patient and talking with her it was decided by Paramedics that patient fainted due to an emotional response by patient and there was no allergic reaction or anaphylaxis to report, nor any injury sustained by patient after fainting. Patient was quickly back to normal, and she verbally declined ambulance. Patient stated that she felt fine and that she was going to do some shopping and return home to relax.
None stated.

Vital signs on arrival were 176/110, she was placed on a litter and history obtained. She was assessed and continued to be observed with sequential vital signs. She denied any tunnel vision, and nausea or any bowel or bladder urgency. Her f/u vital signs were 132/95, HR 85, and 100% O2 on room air. Patient was given water, and was observed for a total of 40 minutes. Final vital signs were 108/72. Patient stated that her symptoms resolved, her cheeks were flushed, her throat tingling was gone, and she stated that she felt better. Patient was able to ambulate off of the site.

Transcription of a text I sent to my colleagues:  Hi all--I'm not sure who has received the second vaccine, but I wanted to update as to my experience.  I got sick with the first one from about 4ish hours after until the next mid morning maybe?  Then I felt bad again that second night.  I had my vaccine (second) yesterday at 4 PM, and I felt OK going to bed but had a pretty pitiful night.  I woke up at 5 AM and I felt horrible.  That felt like someone took a pair of metal cymbals and slammed them together on my head.  The tinnitus was strong.  I also had body aches and joint pain and felt like I had the flu.  I felt a little better around 1 PM, but felt bad again around 330.  Now I'm miserable again with terrible body aches and chills (this was at 7:38 PM).  I'm sure I will feel better in the morning, just wanted to share my experience."  Sadly, since then, I have had tinnitus with a metallic ringing in both ears along with hearing loss.  I had some vertigo one day but unsure if this was related.  The tinnitus makes me very sad.  I am a hospitalist and am happy to have been vaccinated, still.  It has been 2 months today, and it remains, unrelenting.  It is worse in the morning and at night.  The hearing loss is difficult.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had severe nausea and vomiting. I was very sensitive to smells (i.e.: jerk sauce, eggs). I started vomiting every hour from 1:30pm to 7pm the following day, Friday 3/12/21. I would NOT recommend this vaccine or get it again!

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Middle of the first night following the administration of the vaccine, I woke up with notable lower back and hip pain that became increasingly severe over the next 7 days. On Days 5-Day 7 I also developed a rash on my torso and chest. Did not itch or cause discomfort and resolved within days of onset. By the end of the week, I was literally forced to lay flat on the floor all day.  I was completely floor-ridden Day 7-Day 10 .  Pain was predominantly on the lower right side, hip, glute, thigh...had some tingling on top of right foot. This pain most definitely interfered with my daily routine.  Could not get comfortable, could not exercise, could not sleep well. I eventually took my  meals on the floor....only up to use restroom and shower.  From Day 10- Day 12 things very slowly started to improve with complete resolution by the 2 week mark.  It was as if the shot caused my muscles to spasm so badly that my back was thrown completely out?  Or I had some kind of systemic inflammatory process that triggered my low back pain? I NEVER suffer from this kind of debilitating back pain . Typically hike 3- 5 miles per day.  Was extremely bizarre timing and perhaps it was a coincidence? However the sudden onset of this issue in conjunction with the timing of the shot seemed important. I was able to treat pain with Tylenol, muscle relaxers, and lots of rest.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 2 hours after receiving the vaccine on Sunday, I had significant fatigue and sensitivity to light with watery eyes and a headache and was in bed all day. The next morning on Monday I woke with a pressure headache that was kept at bay with Advil. The headache stayed the same on Tuesday and Wednesday. By Thursday the headache was so uncomfortable I was having trouble working. It stopped responding to Advil and the pressure continued to increase on both sides of my head with sharp, shooting pains throughout that would come and go with the constant pressure. By Friday, I couldn?t co to use work and ended up calling into my PCP and advising them that I had a migraine that was very different from my normal migraines that I get (pain on left side behind eye, very nauseous, sensitive to light, always responds to OTC meds) and it wouldn?t respond to Advil and asked them to call in something. They called in generic version of Imitrex that evening; but since this migraine was so different than my normal pattern, I went to the ER on Saturday. They did a CT scan to make sure there were no  brain bleeds and gave me IV magnesium and steroids. I declined the torodol and Benadryl. The headache was still there, but bearable finally when I left. It got worse again that evening and I ended up taking the imitrex at 3am and falling asleep, only to wake up at 7am with a skull splitting feeling. That feeling stayed for the next 4 days, slowly getting less intense. I was unable to workout any of these days (I workout for about an hour daily for the past 3 years) because it was extremely exacerbated by activity. I was not hungry. Finally on Thursday I felt more like my normal self but the headache remained slightly and now on Sunday all that is left is the sharp, shooting pains that come every so often and light sensitivity.
LAB_DATA: CT scan - normal for age . Normal blood pressure, normal pulse. No fever.

The volunteer chose a landing mark for the needle which when stuck into my shoulder joint area, hit something, so he immediately withdrew that needle.  He then took a new second needle and chose a 2nd landing mark that was close to the first needle "stick" and delivered the vaccine.  I felt immediate burning  and that continued for much of the day.   The burning proceeded into intense pain.  I returned to the Senior Center at 7:30 a.m. the next morning and reported the error the volunteer made and showed the head nurse the bruise that was high - at my upper arm - and nearly on my shoulder.  The head nurse said it was "high."   She asked me what I wanted her to do.  I responded that she should report the error and I would like it documented, as I was now afraid I might have endured a shoulder/joint injury.  I also called the health department and the Covid-19 Help Line  and reported the error.  I had two days of intense pain, where I could not physically, not just the excruciating pain, lift my arm.  I emailed an Orthopaedic doctor who specialized in shoulders and made an emergency apmt with him.  I also made an apmt with my primary.  My ortho doctor is treating me for SIVRA, I am on anti-inflammatories, I am having physical therapy on my left shoulder, as there is constant pain.  I am scheduled for return visits to my orthopaedic doctor and this appears to be a concern as far as damage, time course and outcome.  I hope the head nurse DID report the injury to my shoulder area.  She promised to record the event in "my file,"
LAB_DATA: The ortho doctor took an X-ray to rule out any shoulder issue separate from the poorly placed landing mark of the volunteer and there was no issue except for that caused by the 2 needles. Examinations and ongoing testing.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had immediate, but manageable pain, at the site of the injection. It gave me a sore upper arm and stiff neck. I ignored all symptoms and went about my day. Showed houses, wrote an offer, and went to bed about 10:30pm. I was awakened from a deep sleep at 4:30 am (about 14 hrs after the vaccination) with an all-over body sensation that continued to get worse. I tried to come up with a word to describe what my body was feeling. It was like all my insides were being, "scrambled" and then continued to almost burn. I was not right at all. I got out of bed, woke my husband, went to the bathroom and began to faint. I made sure to get to the floor and crawled back to beside the bed with a complete strangling feeling to my heart. It was as if I might have been having a heart attack. My husband got me a chewable baby aspirin (kind of a joke between us). I took it (could not have swallowed a drink at this point). Within a few minutes, my heart felt like it released. It was scary and painful and over almost as quickly as it started. My heart almost felt bruised after. I went to the Dr again the next day to make sure I was ok. Doctor did an EKG and found my heart to be ok. I will need you to verify what lot number and Dose number in the series. I do not have this information.
LAB_DATA: EKG on heart was determined to be normal
OTHER_MEDS: No prescription medications and I had stopped taking any supplements for my physical. I do Botox wrinkle treatments on my face every 90 days. That would be the only foreign substance that could have been in my system that day.
CUR_ILL: No known illnesses. My appointment was for a physical
ALLERGIES: No known allergies. I do not do well with anesthesia

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Immediate (non-severe?) allergic reaction. I received the first dose of the Modern covid vaccine, injected into my left arm. I went to sit for the mandatory 15 minute "observation" period, sitting with a couple of my coworkers who were being vaccinated at this time as well. After approximately two minutes, I started feeling a little light-headed and had slight difficulty breathing. I mentioned it to my coworkers and they suggested I take off my mask (masks were required for everyone). I did so and took a couple deep breaths which made me feel better. I put my mask back on and continued chatting with my coworkers. About 5 minutes later I felt the same, slight difficulty breathing again, but thought it was probably due to my mask, so I repeated - mask off, deep breaths - and felt better. As a precaution, I stayed in the observation area for 30 minutes with one my coworkers, but did not experience any other problems. Feeling a little shaky but otherwise okay, I left at that point and walked to my car. Once in the car, I took off my mask and took more deep breaths. Feeling okay, I started my drive home (approx 7 minutes). About halfway on the drive I felt a slight difficulty in breathing again, so I rolled down the window, took deep breaths. Arriving home, I told my husband I felt "a little weird". My throat felt slightly swollen, the back of my neck felt stiff, my lips felt a bit numb, my face felt tingly and my jaw felt tight. It was about 2:45 at this point. I felt the outside of my throat with my fingers and realized my tonsils were quite swollen. My husband felt them, too, and agreed. However, nothing was visibly swollen in my face or neck, only felt inwardly. I still felt a bit shaky and had an occasional metallic taste in my mouth. I drank some water and laid down, with my feet slightly elevated. My husband stayed with me, both of us monitoring my symptoms in case anything got worse and medical attention was needed, but nothing got worse. My symptoms stayed at this level for the next few hours. I sat up occasionally and continued to drink water. I would get occasional waves of slight difficulty in breathing, but would take deep breaths and that would help. My airway never felt constricted, I just felt like I need a bit more oxygen. By early evening, I was feeling a little tired, but was able to eat dinner without problem and by about 8pm I was feeling a bit better. The swelling in my tonsils had subsided a little at this point and the waves of difficulty in breathing were getting much less often and milder. I slept through the night without problem. In the morning, however, I did not feel very well. I felt quite fatigued and had a little difficulty breathing again, but no worse than before. My arm was pretty sore from the injection, but no other symptoms had developed otherwise. By about 11am, I started feeling better, and by about 1:00pm I felt much better. I had low energy, but I otherwise felt good the rest of the day and slept fine again that night. This morning (day two) I again felt some fatigue and had a little difficulty breath at times, but by mid-morning I felt much better and have continued feeling a little low in energy, but otherwise okay so far. It is now 6:30pm on day two.
Chills, General unwell feeling, runny nose
Swelling, numbness, and pain in side and back

The pt's pertinent medical history, concurrent conditions and concomitant medications were not provided. On or around 10-JAN-2014, the pt was inoculated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster) (strength, dose, route of administration, anatomical location, lot # and expiration date were not reported). shortly after receiving zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, the pt suffered a sudden and severe sore throat, a metallic taste in her mouth and pain when swallowing. she was diagnosed with postherpetic geniculate ganglionitis (geniculate ganglionitis). As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, her symptoms have resulted in physical limitations which were not present prior to using this vaccine. She also experienced mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of her condition and sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence, she suffered serious, progressive, permanente and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. Pt had suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. At reporting time, pt was not recovered from geniculate ganglionitis and this event was considered to be related to zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine. Geniculate ganglionitis was considered to be a disabling event.

The reporter stated that the patient got the Covid vaccine the previous day, he had a history of prostate cancer from about 10 years ago and was treated by radiation, the radiation had caused capillaries in the penis to be fragile and so sometimes when he urinate, he urinate blood or little blood clots, neurologist was aware of it, cardiologist was aware of it but they did not treat it, they just waited for it to resolve itself. He was also on Eliquis for a Atrial fib so the previous day when we came home after he got the vaccine, he was bleeding with the clots and with the bloody urine which he had done in the past. The outcome of events, sweats, fatigue, throbbing headache, chills, muscle pain and fever of 101.3 were considered not resolved at the time of this report.  The outcome of COVID was unknown. SYMPTOM_TEXT: they look like a beehive stung them; reaction is becoming systemic, because the patient now has a terrible itching everywhere, and they look like a beehive stung them; COVID arm; looks like bleeding under the skin; big area that was red and as big as the front part of her arm with a wider irregular shape, about a half inch crescent, dark subcutaneous reaction; as a severe allergic reaction; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 79-year-old female who received the second dose of Moderna's COVID-19 (mRNA-1273) vaccine and experienced the following:  covid arm (Vaccination site reaction), looks like bleeding under the skin (Vaccination site bruising), big area that was red and as big as the front part of her arm (Vaccination site erythema), the patient now has a terrible itching everywhere (Generalised pruritus), and they look like a beehive stung them (Generalized urticaria), and the reaction is becoming systemic, a severe allergic reaction (Allergy to vaccine).  The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use included high blood pressure medication (not specified),  curcumin, and acetylsalicyclic acid.  On 07 JAN 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number not provided).    On 04 FEB 2021, approximately five days prior to the onset of the symptoms, the patient received their second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: 032L20A) intramuscularly in the left deltoid for the prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.    On 08 Feb 2021, the patient experienced the events covid arm; mother of all covid arms; looked like hell, really bad; looked like bleeding under the skin; big area that was red and as big as the front part of arm with a wider irregular shape, about a half inch crescent, dark subcutaneous reaction; looked like bleeding under the skin; very tremendous reaction, but it does not hurt.   On 11-Feb-2011, the red subcutaneous reaction deepened and started to migrate almost immediately, and slowly migrated 5-6 inches to the bottom of the arm near the elbow. The reporter stated the reaction seemed to be getting better; it was not getting any worse, but was worried it may turn into cellulitis or gangrene. On an unknown date, the patient consulted with a dermatologist for the "Covid arm" and the reporter stated that the reaction was becoming systemic because the patient now had terrible itching everywhere, and they looked like a beehive stung them. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Major allergic reaction to the shot; Heat all over her body; Foggy head; Heavy right arm; Shooting pain under the breast; Left ear and face itching, itching spread all over body; Clogged ears; A spontaneous report was received from a 69-year old female consumer who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced major allergic reaction to the shot, heat all over her body, foggy head, heavy right arm, shooting pain under the breast, left ear and face itching, itching spread all over body and clogged ears.   The patient's medical history included asthma and anaphylactic shock with Sulfa medication. No relevant concomitant medications were reported.   The patient received the first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273, (Lot/Batch No. 031M20A) on 26-Feb-2021 intramuscularly in the right arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.    The patient reported after her first shot, she did stay in the office for 30 minutes and after she left within the hour after receiving the shot, she had a major allergic reaction. The patient felt heat all over her body, foggy head, right arm was heavy, shooting pain under breast, felt ear and face was itching. Then itching spread all over the body, and ears clogged up. A 63-year-old male patient received first dose of bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, Formulation: Solution for injection, Batch/ lot number: EL9269, Expiration date: Unknown, NDC number: Unknown), via an unspecified route of administration in left shoulder area on 08Feb2021 16:30 at single dose for COVID-19 immunisation. The patient's medical history included ongoing asthma for about 60 years, ongoing high blood pressure for about 3 years and was on blood pressure medication, issues with thyroid for about 3 years and was on thyroid medication (ongoing). Concomitant medication included ongoing thyroid medication. Patient's medical history (including any illness at time of vaccination) was none. Family medical history relevant to adverse events was none. Prior vaccinations (within 4 weeks) was none. Adverse events following prior vaccinations was none. Additional vaccines administered on same date of the Pfizer suspect was none. The patient experienced bad prostate, bladder infection, sore arm on an unspecified date in Feb2021. On 11Feb2021, the patient experienced body aches, feeling worse, shivers, headache, mild fever. It was reported that, caller received his first dose of bnt162b2 on Monday 08Feb2021. He's reporting adverse events and would like to know: If he takes Tylenol to treat his symptoms, would it decrease the effectiveness of the vaccine or not. Also, if he were to go for a COVID-19 viral test, would the fact that he was received the vaccine interact with the test and cause a false positive result or not. Patient was reporting that yesterday, day 4, he started with body aches, headache, and "when he got in bed, he had chills and shivers real bad, little chilly" so possibly a mild fever. Enquired could these all be side effects of the vaccine or not. If he go for the COVID test - would it be positive or not. He also states he has a history of asthma and has been hypervigilant about avoiding COVID infections. Caller, reporting on the COVID vaccine and who explains that he got the first shot on Monday and he had a mildly sore arm- this lasted 2-3 days, no big deal. Then 5 days later he had really bad body aches and a headache. He went to bed cause he was feeling worse but before going to bed he noticed he had shivers really bad, uncontrollably almost which lasted over an hour. He presume they are fairly normal side effects but wants to confirm this could happen after five days. Also, he was told not to take Aspirin or Tylenol before getting the vaccine because it could affect the efficacy, but he wants to know could he take a Tylenol now 5 days later for the headache and body aches. He was better now than he was doing. Caller clarified the event was 4 days after the shot, the shot was Monday and events started Thursday. On Thursday evening, 11Feb2021, was when he had the bad body aches, headache, and shivers. At this point he still has the headache and body ache. He felt like, last night, he had a fever, but he didn't check it. At the same time, he had the chill and the shivers. Those feelings were resolved by this morning. Caller received COVID vaccine on 08Feb2021-Internal Infection-Bad prostate and bladder infection. Adverse events did not require visit to emergency room and physician office. No relevant tests. No investigation assessment. The events were considered as non-serious by the consumer. The outcome of the events mild fever, feeling worse, bad prostate, bladder infection was unknown, recovering for body aches, headache, recovered on 12Feb2021 for shivers, recovered on an unspecified date in Feb2021 for sore arm.

The patient's medical history was not reported. The patient was on unspecified concomitant medications. The patient stated he has been taking the same medications for several years, and he has had no problems with those. The patient did not receive any other vaccines on the same day. The patient had his first Pfizer COVID-19 shot on 22Jan2021. He was due for his second shot on 12Feb2021. After he had the first shot, his body got itchy all over and it was still itchy. He also had little tiny pimples on his skin, and it was very uncomfortable. He was wondering if this was a known reaction to the product. He had no idea what to do to relieve the itching. He got the vaccine on 22Jan2021, and the itching started either the next day or two days after getting the vaccine. His body became very itchy, and he was itchy all over. He was developing little red like pimples all different parts of his body; itchy bumps. The itching and pimples having continued through to now, and it seemed to get even more itchy in the evening at bedtime. Last night (unspecified date), he had it on the top of his feet down there, on the top and in between his toes. Those itchy bumps were all over, and he did not know if that was the Pfizer shot.  The patient tried different anti-itch creams on it, and that relieved it for a while, but then it came back. He used clobetasol propionate, but it had not worked. They stopped itch for a while but then it does not help. He tried some just plain anti-itch cream (clarified as Gold Bond Anti-Itch Cream) to stop the itching. patient received Adacel vaccine at the age of 9 years and 10 months in error which should be administered at 11 years of age/no AE; Initial information regarding an unsolicited valid non-serious case was received on 25-Feb-2021 from a Nurse via Agency (Reference number- 00493530) and transmitted to Sanofi on 25-FEB-2021.  This case involves a 9 years 10 months old female patient who was vaccinated with first dose 0.5 mL DIPHTHERIA-2/TETANUS/5 AC PERTUSSIS VACCINE [ADACEL] [Strength- Standard] in error which should be administered at 11 years of age (batch number and expiry date not reported) lot number not reported via unknown route in unknown administration site for prophylactic vaccination on 01-Jul-2016 (Inappropriate schedule of product administration).  At the time of reporting, the patient was 14 year-old and the nurse asked if patient could receive next Adacel vaccine.  The patient's past vaccination(s) included TD and DTAP for prophylactic vaccination. The patient's past medical history, medical treatment(s) and family history were not provided.  Concomitant medications included HEPATITIS B VACCINE (HEPATITIS B VACCINE) for prophylactic vaccination.  No adverse event reported at the time of reporting.  Reporter wanted to know if they need to revaccinate the patient at 11 years old. Nurse was at lunch at the time of the call. Left contact information with the front desk. If the nurse calls back, it was mentioned please provide information from "Catch Up Schedule" standard. It was not sure if it was relevant as it sounded like from the call that the patient may have already had her TD and DTAP vaccines for prophylactic vaccination  Product used: Used; First time product used: Yes; Still using product: No  It was a case of actual medication error due to inappropriate schedule of product administration (latency was on same day).  This suspected adverse reaction report is submitted and classified as a medication error solely and exclusively to ensure the marketing authorization holder's compliance with the requirements set out in Directive 2001/83/EC and Module VI of the Good Pharmacovigilance Practices. The classification as a medical error is in no way intended, nor should it be interpreted or construed as an allegation or claim made by the marketing authorization holder that any third party has contributed to or is to be held liable for the occurrence of this medication error.  There will be no information available on batch number for this case.

cerebral infarction/Dizziness and Giddiness/blurry vision, altered speech, headache, difficulty with speech; hypertension; Meniere's Disease affecting the left ear/ moderate Sensorineural Hearing Loss in left ear; severe Sensorineural Hearing Loss in right ear; Information has been received from a lawyer regarding a case in litigation referring to a male patient (pt) of unknown age. Information about concurrent condition, medical history and concomitant medication was not reported. On or around 14-JAN-2015, the pt was inoculated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) (strength, dose, route, lot # and expiration date were not reported) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). Shortly after receiving the vaccine, the pt suffered blurry vision, altered speech, headache, difficulty with speech and was diagnosed with dizziness and giddiness, hypertension, cerebral infarction, severe sensorineural hearing loss in right ear and moderate sensorineural hearing loss in left ear and Meniere's Disease affecting the left ear. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt's symptoms had resulted in physical limitations not present prior to using the vaccine. The pt also experienced mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of his condition. As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of the product, the pt suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt had suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of all the events was not recovered. The causality assessment was considered as related by the lawyer.  All the aforementioned events were considered to be disabling by the lawyer. Upon internal review, cerebral infarction, severe sensorineural hearing loss in right ear and moderate sensorineural hearing loss in left ear and Meniere's disease were determined to be medically significant.

My eyes are a mess / Skin around my eyes became very red; Fever; My eyes are still swollen; 5 days after the shot I got COVID; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of erythema periorbital in a patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   Previously administered products included Shingrix (1st dose received on 27th August 2020, refer case US2021AMR007178).   On 29th November 2020, the patient received the 2nd dose of Shingrix. In December 2020, an unknown time after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced coronavirus infection. On an unknown date, the patient experienced erythema periorbital, fever and eye swelling. On an unknown date, the outcome of the erythema periorbital, fever and coronavirus infection were unknown and the outcome of the eye swelling was not recovered/not resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the erythema periorbital, fever, coronavirus infection and eye swelling to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: With 1st dose of Shingrix, the patient had an eye reaction and doctor did not think it was due to the vaccine. It lasted on and off about a month or more. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I?ve been taking blood pressure medicine for approximately 12 years and all has been well, The medication has consistently maintained me in the normal, that is safe, range. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my second dose at 12:15pm on 03/06/2021. By about 9-10pm I began feeling chills. I went to bed and my body wouldn?t warm up under the covers. I woke up around 1:16am feeling very hot. I was running a fever of about 102F. After removing the covers and using a cold compress it dropped to the 99F range and fluctuated quickly between about 98.7F-99.9F. She had a small emesis x2. Patient then laid down on the stretcher and stated she was feeling better. Patient was taken to the ED via stretcher, she was alert and responsive.
LAB_DATA: 57-year-old female here with syncope after being the Covid shot.  She arrives afebrile, well-appearing, hemodynamically stable.     Patient's EKG did not show evidence of conduction blocks, Brugada, ARVD, WPW, HOCM, long or short QT interval, acute ischemia.   Fingerstick without abnormality.   Patient with history of vasovagal syncope in the past and this episode seems consistent with this past history of this.  She reports feeling much improved at this time is asymptomatic at this time so low suspicion for serious occult cause of the syncope otherwise.  Patient stated understand return precautions and appeared improved at time of discharge.

The patient's medical history and concomitant medications were not reported. The patient received the vaccine and had been fine. On 05Feb2021, mid afternoon, she went to an urgent care and tested negative for COVID and the flu. On 06Feb2021, she was fine, had a little fever in the morning, but about 3 in the afternoon, she started with pretty severe joint pain from her jaw to her ankles. She was recently diagnosed with non-Hodgkins Lymphoma and they put her on a chemo and a monoclonal antibody. One of the oncologists thinks it was a reaction to the vaccine. Outcome of the events was unknown.    No follow-up attempts are possible; information about batch number cannot be obtained.; Sender's Comments: Based on the limited information currently available, a causal relationship between event non-Hodgkins Lymphoma and BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE) cannot be completely excluded. The case will be reevaluated should additional information become available. The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committees and Investigators, as appropriate.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within a few minutes after Jannsen vaccination, in the observation area, patient called attention to staff. A few nurses arrived immediately including this RN. She became dizzy, nauseated. Emesis bag but no vomiting occurred. Vital Signs taken with Systolic BP in the 60's, mild bradycardia, significant clamminess. Patient endorses usally HR higher than this. Patient then developed a period of absence x 2, similar to absent seizure. Patient was laid on a stretcher with slow improvement in S-BP to 111 and clamminess. Given the significant hypotension and suspected absence seizures, staff had already call 911. Patient reported only having some popcorn and coffee all day with no meaningful intake of food or fluids once patient became more alert. This RN provided 2 bags of chips with salt and 2-16 oz. bottles of water. This RN encouraged intake. Fire, EMS, and Police arrived. Patient refused transport to hospital. Patient agreed to wait until significant other arrived to drive patient home. Patient stayed for about an hour extra to eat and drink with moderate effect. Patient stood up and felt moderately dizzy but patient was able to ambulate to her significant other's vehicle. The team encourage patient to contact and see PCP regarding the absent seizure and encourage rest with hydration and intake at home. Incident report was filed with facility.

Experienced a delayed reaction to vaccine that occurred at 11 p. m.  Administration was at 8:23 a. m. earlier in the day.  Symptoms began as build up of mucous in back of throat and reflux. Very early the next morning symptoms progressed to near inability to swallow,    Took 50 mg of Benadryl which gave a bit of relief.  Very hard to drink the water and get it down with the two pills.  The symptoms included swollen lips and inside of the mouth swelling.  Went to the emergency room at the Clinic  at 7:30 a. m.   I was given 60 mg of Prednisone, Pepsid to coat the stomach re the steroids. Was sent home with prescription for epi pen, medrol dose pack, Pepsid and Zyrtec.  Symptoms improved except for swelling of lips.  However, on 3/11/21, despite taking the medication, the symptoms worsened in terms of renewed lip swell as well as new symptoms of facial flushing and chest flushing.  Symptoms then abated with medication.  On 3/13/21, symptoms flared again with renewed lip swelling, inside and outside check swelling and outside face and chest flushing.  They they abated again with medication.  On 3/14/21, lip swelling renewed as a symptom.  To date, my lips do not feel right but tingly and bloated and irritated.  Saw an allergist this morning who thinks I am allergic to polyglycol a preservative in the vaccine.
LAB_DATA: Awaiting skin testing appointment to be scheduled.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received the second COVID vaccine (Pfizer-BioNTech) on 2/14/21. Within 12 hours of the vaccine, "normal" reaction symptoms occurred including fever, chills, sweating and rigors, which was a shaking feeling in the legs, arms, torso and other areas of the body. These symptoms lasted 1.5 days and then seemed to disappear, only to appear again in waves over 10 days following the second vaccine. On day 10, I had a fever of 101.4.  By 2 weeks out, most of the symptoms had dissipated aside from an internal shaking feeling which moves from the chest to the torso, legs etc. It's different all the time and but muscles are felt vibrating in the body and nearly 1 month later the vibrating symptoms are still present. The vibrating can be described like having an electric toothbrush inside your body.
LAB_DATA: 2 Negative  COVID  tests on 2/23 Negative COVID test on 3/11 Normal EKG on 3/12

The patient had a sore arm for about a day after the vaccination.  Six days later the left arm was red and swollen, inside forearm four inches down below the elbow it was stinging, slightly swollen, just to a soft touch she felt lumps of swelling. The patient went to the emergency room and had blood work and an ultrasound.  The emergency room doctor told her that she had a blood clot in the left forearm four inches down below the elbow. The lab test done at the emergency were blood work and ultrasound.
